                                                                        <section class="region region-content">
      

<div  class="ds-1col node node-page view-mode-full clearfix">

  
  <div class="field field-name-body"><p>Below is a selection of recent press releases and news items. If you would like to be included on our media list to receive press releases from the Whole Grains Council, please contact <a href="mailto: katherine@oldwayspt.org">Katherine Kelley</a> (617-896-4801). </p>

<h2>2023 Selected News and Press Releases</h2>

<p><em><strong><a href="/whole-grains-council-2023-whole-grain-consumer-insights-survey">More Than 75 Percent of Americans Think They Should Increase Their Whole Grain Intake, According to a New Survey From the Oldways Whole Grains Council</a> </strong></em>(August 23, 2023)<br />
2023 Whole Grains Consumer Insights Survey</p>

<h2>2021 Selected News and Press Releases</h2>

<p><a href="/whole-grains-council-2021-whole-grains-consumer-insights-survey"><em>New Survey from the Whole Grains Council Finds More Than Half of Consumers Are Eating More Whole Grains Than They Did Five Years Ago</em></a> (July 28, 2021)<br />
Our 2021 Whole Grains Consumer Insights Survey &#xfb01;ndings show whole grain consumption is on the rise.</p>

<h2>2018 selected news and Press Releases</h2>

<p><em><a href="/whole-grains-council-conference-november-4-6">Whole Grains Council Conference November 4-6</a></em> (June 14, 2018)<br />
This year&#8217;s Oldways Whole Grains Council Conference in Seattle, WA will spotlight cutting-edge food industry trends.</p>

<h2>2017 SELECTED NEWS AND PRESS RELEASES</h2>

<p><em><a href="/best-dietary-change-according-experts-switching-whole-grains">The Best Dietary Change According to Experts? Switching to Whole Grains</a></em> (December 14, 2017)<br />
The Oldways Whole Grains Council recently participated in the Whole Grain Summit in Vienna, Austria, where compelling data showed the huge improvements in public health possible through switching to whole grains. An intensive two-year action plan is underway to encourage global changes.</p>

<p><a href="/nominate-charity-oldways-whole-grains-council%E2%80%99s-good-grains-good-cause"><em>Nominate a Charity for the Oldways Whole Grains Council&#8217;s Good Grains for a Good Cause</em></a> (July 24, 2017)<br />
At the end of Whole Grains Month (Septemeber), one qualifying charity will be randomly selected to win a wealth of delicious whole grain foods. Cast your vote, and help bring more whole grains to more people.</p>

<p><em><a href="/make-all-your-grains-whole-whole-grain-sampling-day-march-29">Make ALL Your Grains Whole on Whole Grain Sampling Day March 29</a></em> (March 7, 2017)<br />
Join the Oldways Whole Grains Council and more than 100 partner organizations (including ShopRite, FoodCorps, Bob’s Red Mill, Hodgson Mills, Bruegger’s Bagels, and many more) in celebrating the 6th annual Whole Grain Sampling Day on Wednesday, March 29, 2017.</p>

<p><em><a href="/new-50-whole-grain-stamp-highlights-products-made-primarily-whole-grains-meet-heightened-consumer">New 50%+ Whole Grain Stamp Highlights Products Made Primarily with Whole Grains, to Meet Heightened Consumer Interest</a></em> (February 28, 2017)<br />
The Oldways Whole Grains Council launches a NEW packaging symbol to showcase whole grain products made primarily with whole grains.</p>

<h2>2016 Selected News and Press Releases</h2>

<p><a href="/newsroom/whole-grains-away-from-home-conference-sept-25-27"><em>Whole Grains Away From Home Conference Sept. 25-27</em></a> (July 13, 2016)<br />
The Oldways Whole Grains Council announces a cutting edge conference to nurture and encourage the proliferation of whole grains in the food service sector.</p>

<h2>2015 selected news and press releases</h2>

<p><a href="/newsroom/most-americans-now-make-half-their-grains-whole"><em>Most Americans Now Make Half Their Grains Whole</em></a> (August 31, 2015)<br />
Our 2015 Whole Grains Consumer Insights Survey details the momentum behind whole grains, with some intriguing data.</p>

<p><em><a href="/newsroom/whole-grains-council-instagram-contest-celebrates-whole-grains-month">WGC’s Instagram Contest Celebrates Whole Grains Month</a> </em>(July 30, 2015)<br />
Show how you “Share the Goodness” of whole grains with others, by posting photos on Instagram, and you may win $500 in cash or a $250 gift card.</p>

<p><em><a href="/newsroom/no-foolin%E2%80%99-whole-grain-sampling-day-is-april-1-2015">No Foolin’! Whole Grain Sampling Day is April 1, 2015</a></em> (February 2, 2015)<br />
Oldways and the Whole Grains Council invites consumers to participate in Whole Grain Sampling Day on April 1, 2015.</p>

<p><em><a href="/newsroom/call-for-industry-to-participate-in-4th-annual-whole-grain-sampling-day">Call for Industry to Participate in 4th Annual Whole Grain Sampling Day</a></em> (January 7, 2015)<br />
Oldways and the Whole Grains Council invites restaurants, foodservice, food trucks, supermarkets and manufacturers to participate in Whole Grain Sampling Day on April 1, 2015.</p>

<h2>2014 selected news and press releases</h2>

<p><em><a href="/newsroom/make-the-switch-contest-winners-announced">“Make the Switch” Contest Winners Announced</a></em> (October 14, 2014)<br />
People across the country voted with their taste buds in the Make the Swtich Contest, organized by Oldways and its Whole Grains Council (WGC). Check out the winners here!</p>

<p><em><a href="/newsroom/whole-grains-conference-tackles-controversial-topics">Whole Grains: Breaking Barriers</a> </em>(July 23, 2014)<br />
Oldways and the Whole Grains Council announce a cutting-edge conference to tackle controversial topics, November 9-11 in Boston.<br />
<br />
<a href="/newsroom/make-the-switch-to-whole-grains-and-win"><em>Make the Switch to Whole Grains and Win!</em></a> (July 8, 2014)<br />
Oldways and the Whole Grains Council are encouraging people everywhere to “Make the Switch” to include more nutritious and delicious whole grains this September, during Whole Grains Month.</p>

<p><em><a href="/newsroom/food-industry-invited-to-participate-in-whole-grain-sampling-day-on-april-2-2014">Food Industry Invited to Participate in Whole Grain Sampling Day </a></em>(January 10, 2014)<br />
Oldways and the Whole Grains Council invites restaurants, foodservice, food trucks, supermarkets and manufacturers to participate in Whole Grain Sampling Day on April 2, 2014.</p>

